88 /* DesignId : MMWL_DesignId_073 */
89 /* Requirements : AUTORADAR_REQ-768 */
90 rlReturnVal_t rlRfDigMonEnableConfig(rlUInt8_t deviceMap, rlMonDigEnables_t* data)
91 {
92  rlReturnVal_t retVal;
93 
94  /* check if deviceIndex is out of defined value */
95  if ((rlDriverIsDeviceMapValid(deviceMap) != RL_RET_CODE_OK) || (RL_NULL_PTR == data))
96  {
97  /* set return error code */
98  retVal = RL_RET_CODE_INVALID_INPUT;
99  }
100  else
101  {
102  /* Package the command with given data and send it to device */
103  retVal = rlDriverExecuteSetApi(deviceMap, RL_RF_MONITORING_CONF_SET_MSG,
104  RL_RF_DIG_MON_EN_SB, (rlUInt8_t*)data,
105  (rlUInt16_t)sizeof(rlMonDigEnables_t));
106  }
107  return retVal;
108 }

360 /* DesignId : MMWL_DesignId_080 */
361 /* Requirements : AUTORADAR_REQ-861 */
362 rlReturnVal_t rlRfTxPowrMonConfig(rlUInt8_t deviceMap, rlAllTxPowMonConf_t *data)
363 {
364  rlReturnVal_t retVal;
365  /* Initialize Command and Response Sub Blocks */
366  rlDriverMsg_t inMsg;
367  rlDriverMsg_t outMsg = {0};
368  rlUInt16_t numSbc = 0U;
369 
370  /* Initialize Command and Response Sub Blocks */
371  rlPayloadSb_t inPayloadSb[RL_MAX_SB_IN_MSG] = {0};
372 
373  RL_LOGV_ARG0("rlRfTxPowrMonConfig starts...\n");
374 
375  /* Construct command packet */
376  rlDriverConstructInMsg(RL_RF_MONITORING_CONF_SET_MSG, &inMsg, &inPayloadSb[0U]);
377 
378  /* check if deviceIndex is out of defined value */
379  if ((rlDriverIsDeviceMapValid(deviceMap) != RL_RET_CODE_OK) || \
380  (RL_NULL_PTR == data))
381  {
382  retVal = RL_RET_CODE_INVALID_INPUT;
383  RL_LOGE_ARG0("rlRfTxPowrMonConfig, Invalid input \n");
384  }
385  else
386  {
387  /* check for NULL pointer */
388  if ((RL_NULL_PTR != data->tx0PowrMonCfg))
389  {
390  /* Fill in-message Payload */
391  rlDriverFillPayload(RL_RF_MONITORING_CONF_SET_MSG,
392  RL_RF_TX0_POW_MON_CONF_SB,
393  &inPayloadSb[numSbc],
394  (rlUInt8_t* )data->tx0PowrMonCfg,
395  (rlUInt16_t)sizeof(rlTxPowMonConf_t));
396  numSbc++;
397  }
398  /* check for NULL pointer */
399  if ((RL_NULL_PTR != data->tx1PowrMonCfg))
400  {
401  /* Fill in-message Payload */
402  rlDriverFillPayload(RL_RF_MONITORING_CONF_SET_MSG,
403  RL_RF_TX1_POW_MON_CONF_SB,
404  &inPayloadSb[numSbc],
405  (rlUInt8_t* )data->tx1PowrMonCfg,
406  (rlUInt16_t)sizeof(rlTxPowMonConf_t));
407  numSbc++;
408  }
409  /* check for NULL pointer */
410  if ((RL_NULL_PTR != data->tx2PowrMonCfg))
411  {
412  /* Fill in-message Payload */
413  rlDriverFillPayload(RL_RF_MONITORING_CONF_SET_MSG,
414  RL_RF_TX2_POW_MON_CONF_SB,
415  &inPayloadSb[numSbc],
416  (rlUInt8_t* )data->tx2PowrMonCfg,
417  (rlUInt16_t)sizeof(rlTxPowMonConf_t));
418  numSbc++;
419  }
420 
421  if (numSbc > 0U)
422  {
423  /* setting num of sub-block to inMsg */
424  inMsg.opcode.nsbc = numSbc;
425 
426  /* Send Command to mmWave Radar Device */
427  retVal = rlDriverCmdInvoke(deviceMap, inMsg, &outMsg);
428  }
429  else
430  {
431  retVal = RL_RET_CODE_INVALID_INPUT;
432  RL_LOGE_ARG0("sub block is NULL\n");
433  }
434  }
435 
436  return retVal;
437 }

823  (rlUInt8_t* )data->tx2IntAnaSgnlMonCfg,
824  (rlUInt16_t)sizeof(rlTxIntAnaSignalsMonConf_t));
825  numSbc++;
826  }
827 
828  if (numSbc > 0U)
829  {
830  /* setting num of sub-block to inMsg */
831  inMsg.opcode.nsbc = numSbc;
832 
833  /* Send Command to mmWave Radar Device */
834  retVal = rlDriverCmdInvoke(deviceMap, inMsg, &outMsg);
835  }
836  else
837  {
838  retVal = RL_RET_CODE_INVALID_INPUT;
839  RL_LOGE_ARG0("sub block is NULL\n");
840  }
841  }
842 
843  return retVal;
844 }
